The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Dec. 2: The rate of inflation rose marginally to 4.32 per cent during the week ended November 19 from 4.2 per cent in the previous week, despite fall in the prices of essential items and industrial fuel. Although prices of vegetables, edible oil, tea, cement and industrial fuels, like naphtha and furnace oil, declined, it failed to arrest the rise in inflation rate. Prices of eggs, poultry chicken, soybean, beer and alcohol firmed up due to higher demand for these products in winter.

 Mumbai, Dec. 2: Gold prices today soared by Rs 165 per 10 grams to scale life-time closing highs at Rs 7,585 on the bullion market. Pure gold rose by Rs 170 to Rs 7,625 per 10 grams. Silver, too, logged a new record close at Rs 12,650 per kilo. In London, gold rose to a 22-year high as investors bought bullion as a hedge against inflation and as an alternative to stocks and currencies.

 Mumbai, Dec. 2: The country?s forex reserves declined by $4 million to $142.17 billion during the week ended November 25 against $142.18 billion in the preceding week.

 Mumbai, Dec. 2: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) has imposed a penalty of Rs 1 lakh on Ispat Industries for violating the listing agreements and regulations.

 Mumbai, Dec. 2: Dabur India Ltd today informed the Bombay Stock Exchange that it has fixed the exit price for Balsara Home Products Ltd at Rs 310 per share.




